    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Budgets, High and Low</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Richard W Cookeon his unease at reading about wealthy women, Christy Ferer, who looks for decorating bargains from her chauffeured limousine (Mar 27) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To The Home Section:</p>
        <p>It is troubling to see an entire page  (''Making Heaven From Pennies,'' March 27) dedicated to a woman giving tips on stretching budgets while ensconced in her ''vast nine-room apartment'' on Fifth Avenue,  driven from bargain to bargain in a chauffeured limousine.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To The Home Section:</p>
        <p>It is troubling to see an entire page  (''Making Heaven From Pennies,'' March 27) dedicated to a woman giving tips on stretching budgets while ensconced in her ''vast nine-room apartment'' on Fifth Avenue,  driven from bargain to bargain in a chauffeured limousine.</p>
        <p>To Christy Ferer, saving pennies is a game; to many others, it is a depressing necessity, with basic survival of self and family at stake.</p>
        <p>RICHARD W. COOKE</p>
        <p>Hyannis, Mass.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
